<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-002-015 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 634 510</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Dec 10 1991 n1820* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Metrologie lays off 47 in the UK as it rationalises its salesoperations.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metrologie International (Personnel management).andO;Topic:     LayoffSales ManagementRecessionReorganization.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>METROLOGIE LAYS OFF 47 IN THE UK AS ITandM;RATIONALISES ITS SALES OPERATIONSandM;Metrologie UK Ltd, the High Wycombe-based subsidiary of France's MetrologieInternational SA, is making 47 redundancies in a rationalisation of its salesoperations.andP;  The company says that the ongoing recession and tighter marginshave forced its arm, and that the rest of Metrologie on the continent will belooking at some form of reorganisation, although precise financialinformation is not available at present since the group's year-end resultshave yet to be posted to the Paris Stock Exchange.andP;  The UK intends to focuson selected areas of expertise and coporate sales have been reorganised intothree business areas - Digital Equipment Corp kit, new technologies andgovernment.andP;  The company does not intend to drop any products from itsportfolio, but low-cost personal computers will now be channelled throughMetrologie Distribution, while Metrologie Corporate will handle high-endvalue-added sales.andP;  Corporate, formerly Rapid Recall, will continue to supplyDEC systems, and the new technologies sales group is to concentrate on the XWindow terminals from Network Computing Devices Inc.andO;</TEXT></DOC>